Q1. List all files larger than 1MB in the current directory and save the output to a file

find . -type f -size +1M > large_files.txt
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q2. Replace all occurrences of 'localhost' with '127.0.0.1' in config.txt and save as updated_config.txt

sed 's/localhost/127.0.0.1/g' config.txt > updated_config.txt
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q3. Search for lines containing "ERROR" and exclude lines containing "DEBUG". Save results to filtered_log.txt

grep "ERROR" log.txt | grep -v "DEBUG" > filtered_log.txt
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q4. Identify the process with the highest memory usage and terminate it

Step 1: Identify process
ps -eo pid,%mem,comm --sort=-%mem | head

Step 2: Terminate process
kill <PID>

If the process does not terminate:

sudo kill -9 <PID>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q5. Print all available gateways in a sorted manner

ip route | grep default | sort
